title: For Sale:  Hogan H-223 18" Designated Marksman
location: Snohomish, King, Skagit Counties, Seattle, Washington
postcontent:
I have for sale a Hogan H-223 18” barreled “Designated Marksman” rifle.  Hogan used to manufacture all of POF-USA’s rifles before the two companies parted ways.  Hogan Guns holds the patent on these rifles, so they kept manufacturing them, only now under their own brand name.  I’m asking $1599.00 and I’ll pay the transfer fee for you.   These rifles sell for $2399.00 new, and that is without the upgrades that I have done to it.  ** I was digging through my safe and found a complete spare Hogan piston replacement kit (piston, gas plug, and oprod) that is brand new.  Highly doubtful that you will ever need it, but I always looked at it as an insurance policy.  Spare parts for every weapons system is a great idea.  These are normally valued at around $175.00.  I'm not going to have a need for it and would rather not try and list it separately.  So, if you want the kit, add either $50.00 to the total cost, or you pay the transfer fee and it's yours.  **

This Hogan Designated Marksman Rifle come’s with a few modifications, a Larue Tactical RISR, Ergo Grip, Magpul CTR Stock, a Daniel Defense rail mounted sling socket, and Diamond Head BUIS.  I’ll give the buyer the choice of triggers and furniture colors.  I am a certified Armorer on the AR platform and will install a Geissele ALG trigger or SSA if you would rather have that than the stock trigger.  I have other options available in my new parts bin that we can discuss if you wish.  I will also give the buyer their choice of colors for furniture.  I have Magpul OD Green that I can swap out as well as Magpul Black.  There is no charge for the equipment swap.  It also comes with one 30 round Magpul PMAG and a black hard case.

This rifle has perhaps a just under a thousand match grade brass cased rounds down the barrel.  That is nothing for this rifle as it’s going to take you well over a 100k rounds to show any significant wear.  I’m not sure of the exact number, but I still have a few rounds left from the case I had purchased when I originally bought this rifle, so I know it wasn’t over that amount.  It’s a heavy, fluted, Rock Creek barrel that has been “Melonited.”  Great care has always been taken with this rifle.  Every time a rod went down the barrel, it went through a bore guide to keep the chamber protected.  This rifle has been my safe queen.  It doesn’t get used much anymore as I have other projects that I’m currently working on. 

Whether you’re looking for a 3 Gun Competition rifle, or a rifle to mount a scope to and really reach out at distance, this is the one.  It’s build to stand the test of time.  Long enough for it to become a family heirloom if that’s your choice.  These rifles are built with only the best of components.  They aren’t your average “store bought” rifles.  Hogan’s are generally built to order as the people that order them are generally serious shooters.  This rifle will outshoot a Sig Sauer, Heckler & Koch, Ruger, Bushmaster, Windham, Patriot Ordinance Factory, etc. as they are custom builds.  

 I’m not looking for trades at this time, serious buyers only please.  

From the manufacturer:

OPERATING SYSTEM: 
Gas impingement operation
The HOGAN gun system has been designed and manufactured to greatly decrease/eliminate heat, carbon build-up, gas leaks, fouling and wear/tear on operating parts which can have an adverse effect on an operating system. 
Each piece of operating system is hard chrome plated and/or melonite heat treated making them almost self lubricating and act as non stick surfaces making them easy to clean and maintain.

UPPER RECEIVER: 
Billet machined from 7075 aluminum forgings, (aircraft aluminum alloy), into an A3 flattop upper receiver to fit varied handrails or a 1-piece upper receiver to fit our Free Floating Monolithic rail system
Finished in black anodizing.  

CHARGING HANDLE: 
Billet machined from 7075 aluminum bar stock, manufactured with an oversized grip and locking latch. 
Black anodized to Mil-Spec 8625, duo colored with electro less Nickel coating/black anodize to Mil-Spec 9625 or NP3™ coated, (depending on customer preference or firearm design).

HANDGUARDS/RAILS: 
Aircraft aluminum alloy precision machined from 6061 T-6 extrusion Free Floating Monolithic Tactical Monolithic top rail.

BOLT and CARRIER: 
.223 bolt: machined from 9310 steel bar stock, phosphate heat treated to Mil-Spec .223 and mag particle inspected, hard chrome plated.
Carrier: billet machined from single piece of 8620 steel - steel bolt carrier (machined as one piece to leave key in place). Heat treated per Mil-Spec.

HOGAN SPECIFICATIONS: 
Smaller parts like springs, screws and washers are sourced from domestic manufacturers. 
Everything in a HOGAN gun is 100% made in the U.S.A. All raw materials are
manufactured from U.S. steel mills. 
All heat treats, plating/coatings, are completed by U.S. owned and operated manufactures.  All accessory and component parts on weapon systems are from U.S. owned and operated manufacturers. 
All HOGAN weapon systems are 100% pure American made.

BARREL: 
Barrel blanks are supplied by Rock Creek Barrels, Inc. and completed to final specification at Hogan Guns.
Heavy  contour, hand lapped button twisted rifled, 6 fluted to improve rigidity and heat dissipation, reduce weight, improve accuracy by reducing barrel vibration when firing. 
4150 Mil-B-11595 chrome moly vanadium alloy (machine gun rated).
70 Rockwell case hardened heat treated “5R” polygonal barrels are 2 times harder than Mil-Spec and hammer forged barrels. 
Corrosion resistant and 10 times thicker and harder than Mil-Spec chromed lining. The treatment on the barrels causes zero imperfections and is extremely smooth which also enables the barrels to consistently achieve excellent accuracy. 
Chamber: 5.56 x 45 mm NATO (.223 Cal) “5R” polygonal right handed 1x8 twist button rifled barrels.
A1 flash hider muzzle brake and crush washer, which is remarkably effective in recoil reduction but it does not suppress the flash. Made by Hogan Guns.

LOWER RECEIVER: 
Billet machined from 7075-T6 aircraft aluminum alloy with integral oversized trigger guard for use with heavy gloves. 
Wire E.D.M.’d flared Magwell, ambidextrous bolt release lever machined into the lower receiver. Finished in black anodizing.

TRIGGER: 
HOGAN “Gold Standard”™ trigger system, 4.5 lb. non-adjustable pull, (for zero failure) single stage competition trigger. 
Trigger, hammer & disconnector E.D.M.’d from A2 tool steel. Melonite heat treated for long life. 
Pin tubes are black oxide coated 8620 steel. Housing precision machined from 6061 billet aluminum. Deep gold anodize finish. High temp silicone cord base cushions. 
Complete with KNS™ precision non-rotating pins.

WEIGHT:
